name: The Ruinous Powers (Warhammer 40,000 Commander Collector's Edition Precon Decklist)

main.name: Abaddon the Despoiler
main.oracle_text:
Trample
Mark of Chaos Ascendant — During your turn, spells you cast from your hand with mana value X or less have cascade, where X is the total amount of life your opponents have lost this turn.
main.flavor_text: Under his rule, there is but one creed: Chaos shall reign.

card.name: Lucius the Eternal
card.oracle_text:
Haste
Armour of Shrieking Souls — When Lucius the Eternal dies, exile it and choose target creature an opponent controls. When that creature leaves the battlefield, return Lucius the Eternal from exile to the battlefield under its owner's control.

card.name: Lord of Change
card.oracle_text:
Flying, ward {3}
Architect of Deception — When Lord of Change enters, draw three cards.
card.flavor_text: The Lords of Change are Tzeentch's greatest servants. The most powerful of them wield fragments of his power over destiny.

card.name: Knight Rampager
card.oracle_text:
Trample
Frenzied Rampage — At the beginning of combat on your turn, choose an opponent at random. Knight Rampager attacks that player this combat if able.
When Knight Rampager dies, it deals 4 damage to target opponent chosen at random.

card.name: Let the Galaxy Burn
card.oracle_text:
Cascade (When you cast this spell, exile cards from the top of your library until you exile a nonland card that costs less. You may cast it without paying its mana cost. Put the exiled cards on the bottom in a random order.)
Let the Galaxy Burn deals X plus 2 damage to each creature that didn't enter this turn.

card.name: Kill! Maim! Burn!
card.oracle_text:
Choose one or more —
• Destroy target artifact.
• Destroy target creature.
• Kill! Maim! Burn! deals 3 damage to target player.

card.name: Khârn the Betrayer
card.oracle_text:
Berzerker — Khârn the Betrayer attacks or blocks each combat if able.
Sigil of Corruption — When you lose control of Khârn the Betrayer, draw two cards.
The Betrayer — If damage would be dealt to Khârn the Betrayer, prevent that damage and an opponent of your choice gains control of it.

card.name: Keeper of Secrets
card.oracle_text:
First strike, haste
Symphony of Pain — Whenever you cast a spell from anywhere other than your hand, Keeper of Secrets deals damage equal to that spell's mana value to target opponent.
card.flavor_text: To look upon one is to surrender every last shred of self-will.

card.name: Heralds of Tzeentch
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Cascade (When you cast this spell, exile cards from the top of your library until you exile a nonland card that costs less. You may cast it without paying its mana cost. Put the exiled cards on the bottom in a random order.)

card.name: Herald of Slaanesh
card.oracle_text:
Locus of Slaanesh — Demon spells you cast cost {2} less to cast.
Other Demons you control have haste.
card.flavor_text:
"I can show you indulgence without regret, delight without boundaries, gratifications beyond count."
—Sha'ris, Deacon of Lust

card.name: Helbrute
card.oracle_text:
Haste
Sarcophagus — You may cast Helbrute from your graveyard by exiling another creature card from your graveyard in addition to paying its other costs.
card.flavor_text:
"No. No! Not the sarcophagus . . . Khorne damn you, you disloyal curs. JUST KILL ME!"
—Kalos the Ravager

card.name: Forgotten Cave
card.oracle_text:
Forgotten Cave enters tapped.
{T}: Add {R}.
Cycling {R} ({R}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
card.flavor_text: In the hearts of mortals, in the pages of ancient lore, in the deep, forgotten places of the universe . . . Chaos awaits.

card.name: Foreboding Ruins
card.oracle_text:
As Foreboding Ruins enters, you may reveal a Swamp or Mountain card from your hand. If you don't, Foreboding Ruins enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B} or {R}.
card.flavor_text: When the Great Rift opened across the galaxy, many Imperial worlds were lost to chaos.

card.name: Exalted Flamer of Tzeentch
card.oracle_text:
Sorcerous Inspiration — At the beginning of your upkeep, return an instant or sorcery card at random from your graveyard to your hand.
Fire of Tzeentch — Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, Exalted Flamer of Tzeentch deals 1 damage to each opponent.

card.name: Evolving Wilds
card.oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice Evolving Wilds: Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text:
"What are ramparts, what are steeples, what are our machines worth in the teeth of this ceaseless hunger?"
—Magos Varnak

card.name: Drach'Nyen
card.oracle_text:
Echo of the First Murder — When Drach'Nyen enters, exile up to one target creature.
Daemon Sword — Equipped creature has menace and gets +X/+0, where X is the exiled card's power.
Equip {2} ({2}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)

card.name: Dismal Backwater
card.oracle_text:
Dismal Backwater enters tapped.
When Dismal Backwater enters, you gain 1 life.
{T}: Add {U} or {B}.
card.flavor_text: Armageddon has become a site of holy pilgrimage for the Orks: a planet where the fighting never stops.

card.name: Deny Reality
card.oracle_text:
Cascade (When you cast this spell, exile cards from the top of your library until you exile a nonland card that costs less. You may cast it without paying its mana cost. Put the exiled cards on the bottom in a random order.)
Return target permanent to its owner's hand.

card.name: Decree of Pain
card.oracle_text:
Destroy all creatures. They can't be regenerated. Draw a card for each creature destroyed this way.
Cycling {3}{B}{B} ({3}{B}{B}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
When you cycle Decree of Pain, all creatures get -2/-2 until end of turn.

card.name: Dark Ritual
card.oracle_text: Add {B}{B}{B}.
card.flavor_text:
"Praise Nurgle! For the plague to have progressed so quickly, truly his blessing must be upon us!"
—Ku'gath Plaguefather

card.name: Dark Apostle
card.oracle_text: Gift of Chaos — {3}, {T}: The next noncreature spell you cast this turn has cascade. (When you cast that spell, exile cards from the top of your library until you exile a nonland card that costs less. You may cast it without paying its mana cost. Put the exiled cards on the bottom in a random order.)

card.name: Crumbling Necropolis
card.oracle_text:
Crumbling Necropolis enters tapped.
{T}: Add {U}, {B}, or {R}.
card.flavor_text: The squad plunged deep into Hive Pandorial, finding only the shambling corpses of those they came to avenge.

card.name: Command Tower
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text: On the Planet of Sorcerers in the Eye of Terror lies the Tower of the Cyclops, the redoubt of Magnus the Red.

card.name: Commander's Sphere
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
Sacrifice Commander's Sphere: Draw a card.
card.flavor_text: The arcane sphere that hovers near Magnus's staff imbues it with the power to transform enemies into mindless chaos spawn.

card.name: Chromatic Lantern
card.oracle_text:
Lands you control have "{T}: Add one mana of any color."
{T}: Add one mana of any color.
card.flavor_text: Used carefully, material has been exposed to the baleful energies of the Warp can be contained to fuel powerful rituals.

card.name: Chaos Warp
card.oracle_text: The owner of target permanent shuffles it into their library, then reveals the top card of their library. If it's a permanent card, they put it onto the battlefield.
card.flavor_text:
"Tzeentch cares not what they were or what they become. Only that they change."
—Kairos Fateweaver

card.name: Chaos Terminator Lord
card.oracle_text: Lord of Chaos — At the beginning of combat on your turn, another target creature you control gains double strike until end of turn.
card.flavor_text: "Charge brothers! Death to the false Emperor!"

card.name: Chaos Mutation
card.oracle_text: Exile any number of target creatures controlled by different players. For each creature exiled this way, its controller reveals cards from the top of their library until they reveal a creature card, puts that card onto the battlefield, then puts the rest on the bottom of their library in a random order.

card.name: Chaos Defiler
card.oracle_text:
Trample
Battle Cannon — When Chaos Defiler enters or dies, for each opponent, choose a nonland permanent that player controls. Destroy one of them chosen at random.

card.name: Brainstorm
card.oracle_text: Draw three cards, then put two cards from your hand on top of your library in any order.
card.flavor_text: The Changer of Ways often sends glimpses of possible futures to his most loyal acolytes, visions that would destroy lesser minds.

card.name: Bloodthirster
card.oracle_text:
Flying, trample
Whenever Bloodthirster deals combat damage to a player, untap it. After this phase, there is an additional combat phase.
Bloodthirster can't attack a player it has already attacked this turn.

card.name: Bloodcrusher of Khorne
card.oracle_text:
Trample
Devastating Charge — Other creatures you control have trample.
card.flavor_text: The Brazen Thunder, foremost of the bloodcrusher legions, are named for the sound they make as they ride into battle.

card.name: Blood for the Blood God!
card.oracle_text:
This spell costs {1} less to cast for each creature that died this turn.
Discard your hand, then draw eight cards. Blood for the Blood God! deals 8 damage to each opponent. Exile Blood for the Blood God!
card.flavor_text: Skulls for the Skull Throne.

card.name: Blasphemous Act
card.oracle_text:
This spell costs {1} less to cast for each creature on the battlefield.
Blasphemous Act deals 13 damage to each creature.
card.flavor_text: In the roiling depths of the Eye of Terror, the bloodthirsty hordes of Chaos Marines plot the downfall of their loyalist brethren.

card.name: Blight Grenade
card.oracle_text:
Destroy target creature.
All creatures get -3/-3 until end of turn.
card.flavor_text: Blight grenades—which induce horrendous effects on their victims—have no impact on the Death Guard, who gladly use the devices in extreme close quarters with the enemy.

card.name: Bituminous Blast
card.oracle_text:
Cascade (When you cast this spell, exile cards from the top of your library until you exile a nonland card that costs less. You may cast it without paying its mana cost. Put the exiled cards on the bottom in a random order.)
Bituminous Blast deals 4 damage to target creature.

card.name: Bile Blight
card.oracle_text: Target creature and all other creatures with the same name as that creature get -3/-3 until end of turn.
card.flavor_text:
"Hold your bitterness deep within, and there let it fester. Let it roil and squirm and churn, until you are filled with bile so poisonous that all you touch falls to ruin."
—Morarion, Daemon Primarch

card.name: Barren Moor
card.oracle_text:
Barren Moor enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B}.
Cycling {B} ({B}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
card.flavor_text: Millennia of constant warfare have left many planets with very little worth fighting over.

card.name: Assault Suit
Aspiring Champion
card.oracle_text:
Menace
Ruinous Ascension — When Aspiring Champion deals combat damage to a player, sacrifice it. If you do, reveal cards from the top of your library until you reveal a creature card. Put that card onto the battlefield, then shuffle the rest into your library. If that creature is a Demon, it deals damage equal to its power to each opponent.

card.name: Great Unclean One
card.oracle_text: Reverberating Summons — At the beginning of your end step, each opponent loses 2 life. Then for each opponent who has less life than you, create a 1/3 black Demon creature token named Plaguebearer of Nurgle.

card.name: Magnus the Red
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Unearthly Power — Instant and sorcery spells you cast cost {1} less to cast for each creature token you control.
Blade of Magnus — Whenever Magnus the Red deals combat damage to a player, create a 3/3 red Spawn creature token.

card.name: Mortarion, Daemon Primarch
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Primarch of the Death Guard — At the beginning of your end step, you may pay {X}. If you do, create X 2/2 black Astartes Warrior creature tokens with menace. X can't be greater than the amount of life you lost this turn.

card.name: The Lost and the Damned
card.oracle_text: Whenever a land you control enters from anywhere other than your hand or you cast a spell from anywhere other than your hand, create a 3/3 red Spawn creature token.
card.flavor_text: The gods of Chaos bestow gifts of mutations upon their champions. Too many of these gifts transform their bearer its mindless, writhing chaos spawn.

card.name: Nurgle's Rot
card.oracle_text:
Enchant creature an opponent controls
When enchanted creature dies, return Nurgle's Rot to its owner's hand and you create a 1/3 black Demon creature token named Plaguebearer of Nurgle.
card.flavor_text: Each plaguebearer is formed from the blighted soul of a mortal slain by Nurgle's Rot.

card.name: Pink Horror
card.oracle_text:
Coruscating Flames — Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, Pink Horror deals 2 damage to any target.
Split — When Pink Horror dies, create two 2/2 blue and red Demon Horror creature tokens named Blue Horror with "Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, this creature deals 1 damage to any target."

card.name: Sloppity Bilepiper
card.oracle_text: Jolly Gutpipes — {2}, {T}, Sacrifice a creature: The next creature spell you cast this turn has cascade. (When you next cast a creature spell, exile cards from the top of your library until you exile a nonland card that costs less. You may cast it without paying its mana cost. Put the exiled cards on the bottom in a random order.)

card.name: Nurgle's Conscription
card.oracle_text: Put target creature card from an opponent's graveyard onto the battlefield tapped under your control, then exile that player's graveyard.
card.flavor_text:
"In the embrace of the great Nurgle, I am no longer afraid, for with His pestilential favour I have become that which I once most feared: Death."
—Kulvain Hestarius of the Death Guard

card.name: Exotic Orchard
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color that a land an opponent controls could produce.
card.flavor_text: In the late stages of a Tyranid invasion, sessile organisms take root in a planet's crust, converting its resources into biomass that can be extracted by the Hive Fleet.

card.name: Be'lakor, the Dark Master
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Prince of Chaos — When Be'lakor, the Dark Master enters, you draw X cards and you lose X life, where X is the number of Demons you control.
Lord of Torment — Whenever another Demon you control enters, it deals damage equal to its power to any target.

card.name: Mandate of Abaddon
card.oracle_text: Choose target creature you control. Destroy all creatures with power less than that creature's power.
card.flavor_text:
"I am the Arch-fiend, the Despoiler of Worlds, and by my hands shall the false Emperor fall."
—Abaddon the Despoiler

card.name: Molten Slagheap
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{1}, {T}: Put a storage counter on Molten Slagheap.
{1}, Remove X storage counters from Molten Slagheap: Add X mana in any combination of {B} and/or {R}.

card.name: Mutalith Vortex Beast
card.oracle_text:
Trample
Warp Vortex — When Mutalith Vortex Beast enters, flip a coin for each opponent you have. For each flip you win, draw a card. For each flip you lose, Mutalith Vortex Beast deals 3 damage to that player.

card.name: Noise Marine
card.oracle_text:
Cascade (When you cast this spell, exile cards from the top of your library until you exile a nonland card that costs less. You may cast it without paying its mana cost. Put the exiled cards on the bottom in a random order.)
Sonic Blaster — When Noise Marine enters, it deals damage equal to the number of spells you've cast this turn to any target.

card.name: Past in Flames
card.oracle_text:
Each instant and sorcery card in your graveyard gains flashback until end of turn. The flashback cost is equal to its mana cost.
Flashback {4}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

card.name: Path of Ancestry
card.oracle_text:
Path of Ancestry enters tapped.
{T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity. When that mana is spent to cast a creature spell that shares a creature type with your commander, scry 1. (Look at the top card of your library. You may put that card on the bottom.)

card.name: Plague Drone
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Rot Fly — If an opponent would gain life, that player loses that much life instead.
card.flavor_text: High-ranking plaguebearers of Nurgle's realm ride into realspace mounted upon Rot Flies—colossal daemonic insects whose appearance is so repugnant it scars the mind.

card.name: Poxwalkers
card.oracle_text:
Deathtouch
Curse of the Walking Pox — Whenever you cast a spell from anywhere other than your hand, return Poxwalkers from your graveyard to the battlefield tapped.
card.flavor_text: Poxwalkers are victims of the Walking Pox, a cruel virulence which rots the infected to death while keeping them conscious.

card.name: Reverberate
card.oracle_text: Copy target instant or sorcery spell. You may choose new targets for the copy.
card.flavor_text:
"That which was, will be. That which will be, was."
—Kairos Fateweaver

card.name: Seeker of Slaanesh
card.oracle_text:
Haste
Allure of Slaanesh — Each opponent must attack with at least one creature each combat if able.
card.flavor_text: War is a dance. And they're looking for partners.

card.name: Sol Ring
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}{C}.
card.flavor_text:
"As Horus once besieged the Sol System, we shall bring the rotting Imperium to its knees."
—Abaddon the Despoiler

card.name: Sunken Hollow
card.oracle_text:
({T}: Add {U} or {B}.)
Sunken Hollow enters tapped unless you control two or more basic lands.
card.flavor_text: Abandoned tunnels and bunkers below the hive city have been secretly recolonized and dubbed the "Forbidden Cities."

card.name: Swiftwater Cliffs
card.oracle_text:
Swiftwater Cliffs enters tapped.
When Swiftwater Cliffs enters, you gain 1 life.
{T}: Add {U} or {R}.
card.flavor_text: In its attempts to mirror Tzeentch's convoluted scheming, the Crystal Labyrinth constantly shifts and rearranges itself.

card.name: Talisman of Creativity
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{T}: Add {U} or {R}. Talisman of Creativity deals 1 damage to you.
card.flavor_text:
"It is my cry that wakes you in the night, and my body that crouches in the shadow. I am Tzeentch and you are the puppet that dances to my tune."
—*The Book of Tzeentch*

card.name: Talisman of Dominance
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{T}: Add {U} or {B}. Talisman of Dominance deals 1 damage to you.
card.flavor_text:
"My Master is the Beginning and he is the End. He is the Master of Mortals, and the core of our Dead Hearts."
—*The Saga of Khorne*

card.name: Talisman of Indulgence
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{T}: Add {B} or {R}. Talisman of Indulgence deals 1 damage to you.
card.flavor_text:
"Embrace your hunger, your lust, your desire. The universe is ours for the taking!"
—Sanctifer LeVay, Cult of the Sacred Union

card.name: Tallyman of Nurgle
card.oracle_text:
Lifelink
The Seven-fold Chant — At the beginning of your end step, if a creature died this turn, you draw a card and you lose 1 life. If seven or more creatures died this turn, instead you draw seven cards and you lose 7 life.

card.name: Temple of the False God
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}{C}. Activate only if you control five or more lands.
card.flavor_text: Chaos renegades always seek to deface and destroy effigies of Imperial piety, replacing them with blasphemous symbols of the Ruinous Powers.

card.name: Terramorphic Expanse
card.oracle_text: {T}, Sacrifice Terramorphic Expanse: Search your library for a basic land card, put it onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: The Cicatrix Maledictum split the galaxy asunder. The raw stuff of Chaos flooded into realspace, transforming whole planets in moments.

card.name: The Horus Heresy
card.oracle_text:
(As this Saga enters and after your draw step, add a lore counter. Sacrifice after III.)
I — For each opponent, gain control of up to one target nonlegendary creature that player controls for as long as The Horus Heresy remains on the battlefield.
II — Draw a card for each creature you control but don't own.
III — Starting with you, each player chooses a creature. Destroy each creature chosen this way.

card.name: The Ruinous Powers
card.oracle_text: At the beginning of your upkeep, choose an opponent at random. Exile the top card of that player's library. Until end of turn, you may play that card and you may spend mana as though it were mana of any color to cast it. When you cast a spell this way, its owner loses life equal to its mana value.

card.name: Tzaangor Shaman
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Sorcerous Elixir — Whenever Tzaangor Shaman deals combat damage to a player, copy the next instant or sorcery spell you cast this turn when you cast it. You may choose new targets for the copy.
card.flavor_text: Tzeentch's beastmen twist reality as they themselves are twisted.

card.name: Venomcrawler
card.oracle_text:
Lifelink
Devourer of Souls — Whenever another creature dies, put a +1/+1 counter on Venomcrawler.

card.name: Warstorm Surge
card.oracle_text: Whenever a creature you control enters, it deals damage equal to its power to any target.
card.flavor_text: Khorne's sole desire is to drown the galaxy in a tide of slaughter. To conquer and kill every living thing, until there is nothing left but spilled blood and shattered bone.

card.name: Wayfarer's Bauble
card.oracle_text: {2}, {T}, Sacrifice Wayfarer's Bauble: Search your library for a basic land card, put that card onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: When Chaos makes a tool that isn't specifically for destroying things, it's usually for finding new things to destroy.

card.name: Worn Powerstone
card.oracle_text:
Worn Powerstone enters tapped.
{T}: Add {C}{C}.
card.flavor_text:
"Power comes in many shapes. But real power does the shaping."
—Abaddon the Despoiler

card.name: Abaddon the Despoiler
card.oracle_text:
Trample
Mark of Chaos Ascendant — During your turn, spells you cast from your hand with mana value X or less have cascade, where X is the total amount of life your opponents have lost this turn.
card.flavor_text: Under his rule, there is but one creed: Chaos shall reign.

tokens.name: Blue Horror
tokens.oracle_text: Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, this creature deals 1 damage to any target.

tokens.name: Tome of the Infinite
tokens.oracle_text: {U}, {T}: Conjure a random card from Tome of the Infinite's spellbook into your hand. It perpetually gains "You may spend mana as though it were mana of any color to cast this spell."
